This paper deals with the task of mining entity synonym sets, which involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves learning algorithms and models, which suggests cs.LG (Learning) as the second likely sub-category. The use of external knowledge bases and distant supervision indicates cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another possible sub-category. The paper also involves neural networks and deep learning, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with data mining and knowledge discovery, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) as a possible sub-category.
